Our plan right now is to allow one character per galaxy and up to 8 characters on an account. We’ve taken this route for a few different reasons, the primary ones are to reduce the amount of muling in the game, as well as an attempt to reduce the number of characters made for the purpose of griefing.<br>
<br>
Muling is where a player will make an extra character just to hold stuff. They log in, they collect stuff from their primary character, and log out. We’re not big fans of muling - if we wanted you to have more objects, we’d increase the size of your inventory! But because other games give so many characters per server, it reduces the perceived value of the character slots, and encourages people to become packrats. <br>
<br>
Second, one of the common ways to grief another player is to create a throw-away character, harass your target, then delete the character. Because we’re allowing only one character per galaxy, it means that this type of activity will be greatly reduced.<br>
<br>
In both instances, what we’re trying to create is a more immersive environment. Reducing muling and griefing characters helps us towards this goal, and we think this will be an important step in accomplishing that.<br>
<br>
We realize one of your concerns is that you can’t try other professions but that is not true with our advancement systems. We don’t lock you into one path. You can chose many different roles. <br>
<br>
Rich Vogel<br>
